## Core System

### u-Kama
The ecological–monetary system that places ecological continuity as the primary constraint on economic activity. u-Kama treats land and living systems as realities, not assets, and designs money as a coordination tool under ecological limits.

### Community is the Operating System
Canonical axiom. Ecological continuity is sustained through human communities bound to place, responsibility, and consequence through time.

---

## Ecological Truth & Memory

### Bio Dynamic Regeneration (BDR)
A non-financial ecological reserve record representing witnessed ecological continuity and regeneration through time. BDR is not priced, traded, redeemed, or consumed. It functions as recorded ecological memory, analogous to gold as a reserve asset but grounded in living systems.

### BDR Era
A completed interval of accumulated, uninterrupted ecological continuity under defined stress conditions. Eras are recorded, not minted as coins.

### Ecological Memory
The durable record that an ecological state persisted through time and stress. Memory accumulates only through survival, never through intent, effort, or expenditure.

### Witnessing
The act that converts ecological existence into ecological continuity through independent corroboration across time.

---

## Tokens & Economic Layer

### BioDollar (BIO)
The utility and participation token of u-Kama. BIO enables access, coordination, validation, and obligation under constraint. BIO does not represent, redeem, or claim ecological truth.

### BDR–BIO Separation Doctrine
Canonical rule. BDR and BIO are strictly separated. No peg, reserve ratio, redemption, pricing reference, or collateral linkage may exist between them.

### WBIO
A wrapped representation of BIO used only at the external membrane for settlement. It carries no authority inside u-Kama.

### BIO Expiry
BIO does not recycle. It either expires or is re-issued from scratch under protocol constraint.

---

## Proof Framework

### Proof of Protection (PoP)
A Boolean determination that a defined ecological state did not cross a declared failure threshold during a defined stress window. Protection recognises restraint, not activity.

### Proof of Regeneration (PoR)
A Boolean determination that a defined ecological state crossed a declared improvement threshold and persisted across stress.

### Failure Threshold
A pre-declared ecological boundary beyond which continuity collapses for the interval.

### Improvement Threshold
A pre-declared ecological boundary that must be crossed and sustained for regeneration to be recognised.

---

## Time, Units & State

### Base Granular Unit (BGU)
A witnessed interval of ecological time that remained intact under defined stress and restraint conditions. BGUs accumulate only through uninterrupted continuity and have no independent value or transferability.

### Ecological Verification Unit (EVU)
A protocol-level verification record that attests to successful witnessing of BGUs. EVUs qualify state transitions but have no independent meaning or value.

### State Machine
The protocol structure through which ecological truth is recognised only as discrete transitions. Nuance exists above the state machine, never inside it.

### Boolean Ecology
The principle that ecological truth at the protocol layer resolves only as pass or fail, because ecosystems cross thresholds, not averages.

---

## Constraint & Issuance

### Ecological Difficulty Adjustment (EDA)
A dynamic issuance governor that increases proof thresholds, verification burden, and risk requirements as ecological integrity increases. Issuance tightens toward zero with success.

### Issuance Window
A defined seasonal or temporal endpoint at which state transitions may be evaluated.

### Activation Gate
The minimum condition required for a project or cell to become eligible for issuance evaluation.

### Issuance Phase
The stage at which BIO may be issued, conditional on satisfied ecological state transitions.

---

## Land, Cells & Authority

### Ecological Cell
The minimum spatial unit at which ecological failure becomes falsifiable under a single authority, stress regime, and threshold set.

### Cell Size
Area-gauged, not shape-defined. Minimum and maximum sizes are set to preserve falsifiability and accountability.

### Cell NFT (Right of Use NFT)
A non-financial NFT encoding recognised stewardship authority and protocol obligation over an ecological cell. It conveys no ownership, yield, pricing claim, or BDR entitlement.

### Right of Use (ROU)
Recognised authority to steward an ecological or cultural asset without owning it, establishing who may act and who is accountable.

### Transfer Under Constraint
ROU reassignment permitted only under defined custodial and protocol triggers. Transfer does not reset ecological history or difficulty.

---

## Roles & Participation

### Custodian
Recognised local or traditional authority responsible for legitimacy, bounds, and permission.

### Steward
Operational actor responsible for day-to-day management, protection, and reporting.

### Witness
A named human participant bound to observation and accountability through time.

### Virtual Observer
A remote participant who witnesses without authority, ownership, or intervention rights.

### Subscriber
A participant who supports continuity through structured obligation rather than donation.

---

## Verification & Integrity

### Trias Testium
The principle that truth is recognised only when preserved by three independent, non-sovereign witness classes: observational, laboratory, and human.

### Observational Witness
Aerial, orbital, or fixed sensors and cameras.

### Laboratory Witness
Soil, eDNA, and biophysical assays.

### Human Witness
Named rangers, transects, and observers.

### AI (Coherence Layer)
Performs contradiction and consistency checks. AI is not a witness and holds no authority.

---

## Use, Extraction & Ethics

### Subsistence Use
Legitimate extraction exercised within declared ecological and cultural bounds under recognised authority.

### Market Leakage
Extraction that escapes subsistence bounds or converts survival use into market depletion. Market leakage collapses Protection.

### Pressure Class
A declared tier that increases verification intensity and obligation without softening thresholds.

---

## Financial Doctrine

### Alignment Bond
A negative-yield participation mechanism that binds capital to obligation without entitlement, yield, or authority.

### Obligation Pool
A financial pool that allocates burden for protection and continuity. It does not back or reference BDR.

### Membrane
The boundary where u-Kama interfaces with external financial systems without allowing reverse influence.

---

## Canonical Distinctions

### Land is a Reality
Land exists independently of title, token, or law.

### Permissions are Not Realities
Title, NFTs, and ROUs are permissions that may change without altering ecological truth.

### Seasons Are Tests
Time is not an invoice. Continuity must survive stress to be recorded.

